# CODEOWNERS — the engine's control surface.
#
# Every path below is part of the trust base that decides whether a stale human approval is
# preserved or dismissed. A change to any of it can, in principle, weaken the merge gate, the
# gates' logic, the model prompt, the "success" echo, the deployment identity, or the
# invariant proofs. Such changes therefore REQUIRE security-team review.
#
# Enforcement: this is enforced by the enrolled ruleset's `require_code_owner_review: true`
# (see deploy/rulesets/enrolled-ruleset.json). It is also mirrored, in CODE, by the Stage-0
# self-governance rule (SELF_GOVERNANCE_GLOBS in src/stages/stage0_hardrules.ts): when the
# engine evaluates a PR against its OWN repo (cfg.selfGovernedRepos) that touches any of these
# paths, it withholds its opinion and dismisses with reason "self_governance" — the engine
# never grades changes to the gates that judge it.
#
# FORKS / DEPLOYERS: replace the placeholder owner `@YOUR-ORG/security-review` below with a
# real team, add your engine repo to `selfGovernedRepos` in config, and enable the CODEOWNERS
# required-review ruleset toggle on your engine repo. The placeholder is inert until you do.
#
# Kept 1:1 in sync with SELF_GOVERNANCE_GLOBS (see the sync-guard test in
# test/self_governance.test.ts).

# Workflows (incl. the fresh-approval fallback) and this CODEOWNERS file itself.
/.github/                          @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# The merge gate (the ruleset that requires approval + status check).
/deploy/rulesets/                  @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# Deployment surface for the engine's identity (Pod Identity / secrets).
/deploy/helm/                      @YOUR-ORG/security-review
/deploy/terraform/                 @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# Thresholds schema + loadConfig.
/src/config/                       @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# Denylist location (config/denylist.yaml per docs/IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md §6).
/config/                           @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# Model prompt is control logic; provider wiring.
/src/model/                        @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# The gates themselves (the ladder + every stage).
/src/stages/                       @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# The entire GitHub boundary: the "success" echo (freshApproval.ts), the only GitHub writer
# (actuator.ts), identity/force-push resolution (pr.ts), and webhook signature verification
# (auth.ts). Directory-wide so future files here are control surface by default.
/src/github/                       @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# Webhook server + event dispatch (what gets routed to the gates at all).
/src/index.ts                      @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# The immutable audit trail (tampering here hides evidence of decisions).
/src/audit/                        @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# The prod-hardening work queue: coalescing/serialization/concurrency-bound scheduling that
# decides when and in what order PR evaluations run (a compromised queue could reorder, drop,
# or duplicate evaluations — as much control surface as the stages it schedules).
/src/runtime/                      @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# Metrics/observability wiring, instrumented directly into the queue + webhook hot path.
/src/observability/                @YOUR-ORG/security-review

# The invariant proofs (no-approve path + check-conclusion guard).
/test/no_approve_path.test.ts      @YOUR-ORG/security-review
/test/check_conclusion_guard.test.ts @YOUR-ORG/security-review
